    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "One thing you can do is hit ctrl-v, ctrl-j to enter a newline without running the input. I think this is part of Bash itself since it also works on the terminal (ctrl-v says to treat the next hotkey as a control sequence and ctrl-j is newline). I haven't had a chance to mess with iTerm2 on this, but maybe it is possible to map ctrl-enter to that double-sequence somehow?\n\nEdit: You can indeed replicate this in iTerm2 at least. Can go to your global shortcut keys and set ctrl-enter to \"Send hex codes\" and then: 0x16 0x0a\n"
  },
